tions.|  \n  \n## Example  \n The following code example illustrates how to specify the serialization mode of a <xref:System.DateTime> object, and the addition of types used by the <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSchemaImporter> when mapping XSD types to .NET Framework types.  \n  \n```  \n<system.xml.serialization>  \n    <xmlSerializer checkDeserializeAdvances=\"false\" />  \n    <dateTimeSerialization mode = \"Local\" />  \n    <schemaImporterExtensions>  \n        <add   \n        name = \"MobileCapabilities\"   \n        type = \"System.Web.Mobile.MobileCapabilities,   \n        System.Web.Mobile, Version - 2.0.0.0, Culture = neuutral,   \n        PublicKeyToken = b03f5f6f11d40a3a\" />  \n    </schemaImporterExtensions>  \n</system.sxml.serialization>  \n```  \n  \n## See Also  \n <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.XmlSchemaImporter>   \n <xref:System.Xml.Serialization.Configuration.DateTimeSerializationSection.DateTimeSerializationMode>   \n [Configuration File Schema](../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/index.md)   \n [\\<dateTimeSerialization> Element](../../../docs/framework/serialization/datetimeserialization-element.md)   \n [\\<schemaImporterExtensions> Element](../../../docs/framework/serialization/schemaimporterextensions-element.md)   \n [\\<add> Element for \\<xmlSchemaImporterExtensions>](../../../docs/framework/serialization/add-element-for-xmlschemaimporterextensions.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[4,525],"nodes":[{"content":"&lt;system.xml.serialization&gt; Element | Microsoft Docs","nodes":[{"pos":[0,57],"content":"&lt;system.xml.serialization&gt; Element | Microsoft Docs","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>system.xml.serialization<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> Element | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,57],"source":"&lt;system.xml.serialization&gt; Element | Microsoft Docs"}]}],"pos":[6,66],"yaml":true}],"content":"title: \"&lt;system.xml.serialization&gt; Element | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".